<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-01T14:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-01T14:49:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/609.</note>
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-01T15:00:00-04:49"><hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 1, 1911—3 <hi rend="smallcaps">p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President has requested permission to embark on an American war
                            vessel pending the arrival of the merchant vessel on Friday. The
                            minister asks instructions.</p>
